Description: Model cylinder jar of limestone: with a roughly shaped rim and concave sides. Hollowing is restricted to a slight depression in the top. The exterior is decorated with specks of black paint.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tomb of Qaa, tomb Q.20 subsidiary burial
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, 15, 28, pl.XXXVIII, 5-6.
